btrplace.model.constraint

Interface SatConstraintChecker<C extends SatConstraint>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AllowAllConstraintChecker, AmongChecker, BanChecker, DenyMyVMsActions, FenceChecker, GatherChecker, KilledChecker, LonelyChecker, MaxOnlineChecker, OfflineChecker, OnlineChecker, OverbookChecker, PreserveChecker, QuarantineChecker, ReadyChecker, ResourceCapacityChecker, RootChecker, RunningCapacityChecker, RunningChecker, SequentialVMTransitionsChecker, SleepingChecker, SplitAmongChecker, SplitChecker, SpreadChecker

    public interface SatConstraintChecker<C extends SatConstraint>
    Check if a constraint is satisfied by a reconfiguration plan.

    The checking process is performed following an event-based approach using an instance of ReconfigurationPlanChecker.

    First, the checker is notified for the model at the origin of the reconfiguration. It is then notified each time an action starts or ends and finally, it is notified about the resulting model.

    Actions notifications are propagated with regards to their starting and ending moment. If an action ends at the same moment another action starts, the notification for the ending action is send first.

    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier
    See Also:
    ReconfigurationPlanChecker
